        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="1">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Prior to performing this service procedure, it is necessary to determine if the vehicle has
                        the old or new type expansion valve (Table 1). The old or new expansion valve can be identified
                        by the vendor part number stamped on the valve. The part number can be determined with the
                        expansion valve in the vehicle.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>This procedure should be performed when installing a new improved expansion valve in a vehicle
                        built between December 5, 1994 and September 8, 1999 for the first time. Vehicles built after
                        September 8, 1999 have the latching jumper wire removed from the harness, and do NOT use relay
                        Part Number 2503522C1.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Replace the expansion valve with the new valve following the procedures in service
                    section CTS-5227 located in Group 16 of the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the lower right instrument panel cover (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0016021">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Replace the air conditioning relay (72) with Part Number 2503522C1. The air conditioning
                    relay is located in the lower relay panel (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0016022">Figure 2</hotlnk>) .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-install the lower right instrument panel cover.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0016021" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9516041.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="150"/>
                <caption>Figure 1.</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>To aid identification, the new relay, Part Number 2503522C1 , has a green color case.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Operate the air conditioning system to verify correct operation.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="2">
            <title>Alternate Service Procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>This procedure should only be used if the air conditioning relay (72) is NOT being replaced
                        with relay Part Number 2503522C1.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Replace the expansion valve with the new valve following the procedures in service
                    section CTS-5227 located in Group 16 of the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Batteries expel gases. Keep sparks, flames, burning cigarettes, or other ignition sources away
                        at all times. Always wear safety glasses and a face shield when working near batteries to
                        prevent personal injury.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the positive battery cable at the battery.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the lower right instrument panel cover (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0016021">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0016022" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9516042.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="150"/>
                <caption>Figure 2.</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the lower relay panel mounting screws from the instrument panel (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0016022">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the air conditioning relay from the electrical harness connector.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the screw that fastens the relay harness connector to the relay panel.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use a plug lock tool to remove the white electrical harness plug lock tab. Pull the lock
                    out of the electrical harness connector.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0016023" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9516043.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="150"/>
                <caption>Figure 3.</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate wire number 77L, in connector position number 4. Use the tool to unlock the
                    terminal tab and pull wire number 77L and terminal out of the relay connector (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0016023">Figure 3</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-install the electrical harness connector lock.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Bend wire number 77L back 180 degrees onto the harness and tape the wire using
                    electrical tape to the harness assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reassemble the relay panel and instrument panel cover following the previous Steps in
                    reverse order.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reconnect the positive battery cable at the battery.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Operate the air conditioning system to verify correct operation.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
